#: ../../source/checks/fit_utils/validate-positive-vector.md:1
msgid "_validate_positive_vector"
msgstr "_validate_positive_vector"

#: ../../source/checks/fit_utils/validate-positive-vector.md:3
msgid "Firma"
msgstr "Signature"

#: ../../source/checks/fit_utils/validate-positive-vector.md:14
msgid "Che problema risolve"
msgstr "What problem it solves"

#: ../../source/checks/fit_utils/validate-positive-vector.md:16
msgid ""
"Valida vettori che devono essere numerici, monodimensionali, finiti e strettamente positivi. In "
"`fit_utils` serve soprattutto per `sigma_y` e `sigma_x`."
msgstr ""
"Validates vectors that must be numeric, one-dimensional, finite, and strictly positive. In "
"`fit_utils` it is mainly used for `sigma_y` and `sigma_x`."

#: ../../source/checks/fit_utils/validate-positive-vector.md:18
msgid "Contratto sugli input"
msgstr "Input contract"

#: ../../source/checks/fit_utils/validate-positive-vector.md:20
msgid "La conversione di base passa per [`_as_float_vector`](../stats_utils/as-float-vector.md)."
msgstr "The base conversion passes through [`_as_float_vector`](../stats_utils/as-float-vector.md)."

#: ../../source/checks/fit_utils/validate-positive-vector.md:21
msgid "Se `expected_shape` e fornita, la forma del vettore deve coincidere esattamente."
msgstr "If `expected_shape` is provided, the vector shape must match exactly."

#: ../../source/checks/fit_utils/validate-positive-vector.md:22
msgid "Ogni elemento deve essere maggiore di zero."
msgstr "Each element must be greater than zero."

#: ../../source/checks/fit_utils/validate-positive-vector.md:24
msgid "Dove viene usata"
msgstr "Where it is used"

#: ../../source/checks/fit_utils/validate-positive-vector.md:26
msgid "in [`lin_fit`](../../moduli/fit_utils/lin-fit.md) per `sigma_y`"
msgstr "in [`lin_fit`](../../moduli/fit_utils/lin-fit.md) for `sigma_y`"

#: ../../source/checks/fit_utils/validate-positive-vector.md:27
msgid "in [`lin_fit`](../../moduli/fit_utils/lin-fit.md) per `sigma_x` quando presente"
msgstr "in [`lin_fit`](../../moduli/fit_utils/lin-fit.md) for `sigma_x` when present"

#: ../../source/checks/fit_utils/validate-positive-vector.md:29
msgid "Come fallisce"
msgstr "Failure modes"

#: ../../source/checks/fit_utils/validate-positive-vector.md:31
msgid "`ValueError` se l'input non supera i controlli di `_as_float_vector`"
msgstr "`ValueError` if the input does not pass the `_as_float_vector` checks"

#: ../../source/checks/fit_utils/validate-positive-vector.md:32
msgid "`ValueError` se la forma non coincide con `expected_shape`"
msgstr "`ValueError` if the shape does not match `expected_shape`"

#: ../../source/checks/fit_utils/validate-positive-vector.md:33
msgid "`ValueError` se e presente almeno un valore minore o uguale a zero"
msgstr "`ValueError` if at least one value is less than or equal to zero"

#: ../../source/checks/fit_utils/validate-positive-vector.md:35
msgid "Perche resta privata"
msgstr "Why it stays private"

#: ../../source/checks/fit_utils/validate-positive-vector.md:37
msgid ""
"E un validatore strettamente legato al dominio del fit lineare del package. Tenerlo interno evita"
" di promettere una semantica generale per tutti i vettori positivi."
msgstr ""
"It is a validator tightly tied to the package's linear-fit domain. Keeping it internal avoids "
"promising a general-purpose semantics for all positive vectors."

